Product description

SmartLight LED Floor Lamp

Whether you are working, studying, or pursuing a hobby, you should have high quality, healthy lighting. SmartLight LED Floor Lamp provides task lighting that is flicker-free and equipped with an Optix glare control lens to reduce eye strain and eye fatigue - allowing you to do what you love, for longer.

Easy touch to adjust the brightness levels

Choose between 5 brightness levels on your SmartLight LED Floor Lamp.

Have a more comfortable experience

Select from 3 color temperatures of white light ranging from warm white to daylight.

Adjusts with Ease

Adjust the sturdy, yet flexible, gooseneck to find the right angle that works for you every time.

Safe for Eyes and Skin

Full-spectrum, UV-free light has passed internationally recognized safety tests for vision and mimics natural daylight to give you a comfortable and healthy lighting experience.


Reduced Eye Strain and Eye Fatigue

SmartLight is flicker-free and equipped with an Optix glare control lens, allowing you to work more efficiently, for longer, and with less eye fatigue.


Versatility of Use

Your SmartLight LED Floor Lamp is perfect for whatever you need. The customizable features and a flexible gooseneck makes this ideal for the office, dorm room, or home, and great for studying, artwork, crafts, and hobbies.


Better Detail

Full Spectrum light provides better detail and truer color, giving you the best light for your best work.

      This is a very good lamp for crafting - it throws a broad enough light and it's plenty bright enough for close work (pottery and ceramic art with detailed surfaces in my case). I had a cheaper one and can't afford the top models, so this is perfect. It's MUCH more stable and sturdy feeling than the old wobbly one from the same company, has excellent warmth options and a good range of brightness settings for when my eyes get tired and is very easy to reach around and change settings - I don't even have to look any more. It's got a decently heavy base and doesn't tip too easily but is light enough that I can also reach around and reposition it with one hand as the task change. The gooseneck is a little but stiff but fine. It could be a lbit taller - I'm working at normal table height - but it hasn't really been a problem. I really love the wealth of very simple-to-change options, it's not fiddly. Good purchase for the price!

    • EJ Honda
      4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Good quality, good lighting options, a bit challenging to put together
      Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2024
      Color: White
      Purchased as part of a Black Friday special, I bought this to supplement our table lamps next to our sofa when I want to read something and our ambient lighting just doesn't cut it. Putting the lamp together (it comes as 5 pieces) was fairly straightforward, except for... See more
      Purchased as part of a Black Friday special, I bought this to supplement our table lamps next to our sofa when I want to read something and our ambient lighting just doesn't cut it. Putting the lamp together (it comes as 5 pieces) was fairly straightforward, except for mounting the base on the lamp pole - that was challenging.

      The base uses a cam that expands out once the lamp post is inserted into the base and over the cam. You use an Allen key to tighten the cam and lock it to the lamp post via friction. It took me four tries before the cam got positioned correctly inside the post to be tightened. The problem is the base is extremely weighty (as you'd want to make the lamp stand sturdy), and thus you have to position the lamp pole upside down so you can access the Allen key socket on the bottom of the base. It was difficult to keep the base fully on the pole while attempting to tighten the cam, all while trying to keep the base straight with the lamp on the post.

      Other than that, the touch controls work nicely, and the choice of lighting from the lamp is a soft white to 'as bright as the sun' white. You should be able to find a setting that works for you and your situation.
      18 people found this helpful

    • Todd T
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Easy assembly, fantastic light output both in intensity and color.
      Reviewed in the United States on February 23, 2025
      Color: Black
      I just received my floor lamp and put it together. Pretty easy assembly with the biggest challenge is feeding a coiled power cable down the tubes. Not too bad, just let gravity help pull the power cord through. It's surprisingly stable on a hard surface floor (not... See more
      I just received my floor lamp and put it together. Pretty easy assembly with the biggest challenge is feeding a coiled power cable down the tubes. Not too bad, just let gravity help pull the power cord through. It's surprisingly stable on a hard surface floor (not carpet).

      The light output is great! REALLY bright at full setting.

      I really like the three color tempertures of the light output. For reading, the first daylight setting must be 5,000 degrees K or higher. I'd put the middle color temperature at a just under 5,000. The warmest color is probably around 3200 K, like an old fashioned incandescent bulb.

      I'm probably going to read using the middle temperture setting and use the highest temp (more daylight tone) for detail work.
